source.name: Use Of Medical Imaging Measures - State
source.description: A list of the state averages for the Use of Medical Imaging quality ratings.  These measures give you information about hospitals' use of medical imaging tests for outpatients. Medical Imaging are Tests that create images of various parts of the body to screen for or diagnose medical conditions. Examples of medical imaging include CT Scans, MRIs, and mammograms.
